5 A BILL
6 TO BE ENTITLED
7 AN ACT
8
9 Relating to crimes and offenses; to amend Section
10 13A-6-142, Code of Alabama 1975, to further provide for the
11 jurisdiction over prosecutions for violations of domestic
12 violence protection orders.
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
14 Section 1. Section 13A-6-142, Code of Alabama 1975, is
15 amended to read as follows:
16 "§13A-6-142
17 (a) A person commits the crime of violation of a
18 domestic violence protection order if the person knowingly
19 commits any act prohibited by a domestic violence protection
20 order or willfully fails to abide by any term of a domestic
21 violence protection order.
22 (b) A violation of a domestic violence protection order
23 is a Class A misdemeanor which shall be punishable as provided
24 by law. A second conviction for violation of a domestic
25 violence protection order, in addition to any other penalty or
26 fine, shall be punishable by a minimum of 30 days imprisonment
27 which may not be suspended. A third or subsequent conviction
28 is a Class C felony.
Page 1

is a Class C felony.
