House Judiciary Reported Substitute for SB173
29 (c) In addition to any other fine or penalty provided
30 by law, the court shall order the defendant to pay an
31 additional fine of fifty dollars ($50) for a violation of a
32 domestic violence protection order to be distributed to the
33 Domestic Violence Trust Fund, established by Section 30-6-11.
34 (d)(1) Except for violations of this section that are
35 under the jurisdiction of the juvenile courts of this state,
36 the district courts of this state shall have exclusive
37 original jurisdiction over prosecutions for violations of this
38 section or any other prosecution for an action that would
39 constitute a violation of this section except as provided in
40 Section 12-12-32.
41 (2) Except for violations of this section that are
42 under the jurisdiction of the juvenile courts of this state,
43 any prosecution for a violation of this section, or any other
44 prosecution for an action that would constitute a violation of
45 this section, that is pending on October 1, 2026, shall be
46 transferred to the district court.
47 (3) This subsection shall not apply to violations
48 arising from a domestic violence protection order issued by a
49 municipal court."
50 Section 2. This act shall become effective on October
51 1, 2026.
